This article is about a White House intern's experience volunteering at a Military Appreciation Event hosted on the South Lawn during the Fourth of July celebration. Despite the rain, the interns were proud and festive, serving food and drinks and assisting with outdoor games. President Donald J. Trump addressed the nation and honored the military service members. The intern had the opportunity to meet the President, Vice President, and First and Second Ladies, and felt their sincere respect and appreciation for the military. The intern admires President Trump's commitment to the Armed Forces. The article concludes with the intern reflecting on the remarkable leadership of the President and the selfless dedication of the military.